HEADWORD: Botcher
<hw>Botch"er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
mends or patches, esp. a tailor or cobbler.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A clumsy or careless workman; a bungler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A young salmon; a
grilse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Botcherly</ent>⟦br⟧
